  "title": "OPERATIONS MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><p>·  Ensure on-time and quality fulfilment while maintaining safety and cost discipline</p><p>·  Plan manpower and capacity to meet business demand</p><p>·  Work closely with Sales and Finance to align operations with commercial commitments</p><p>·  Drive operational improvements, SOPs, and process efficiency</p><p>·  Monitor costs, wastage, and inventory control</p><p>·  Lead, coach, and develop operational teams</p><p>·  Liaising with external parties (MOM, BCA, WSH bizSAFE, SSG etc.) to ensure smooth facilitation of courses</p><p>·  Perform Company HR activity.</p><p>·  Environment scanning, identifying strengths, weaknesses, opportunities, and threats, and creating corresponding strategies and action plans.</p><p><br /><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><p>·  6 yrs of Experience in operations, coordination, or administrative roles</p><p>·  Bachelor’s Degree in Engineering, Technology Management, Business, or related field</p><p>·  Experience in Training Management, Recruitment, Business Development and Operational Management</p><p>·  Possess Certificate of Employment Intermediaries (CEI)</p><p>·  Hands-on, responsible, and dependable leadership style</p><p>·  Demonstrated drive to set and achieve aggressive goals while not compromising on the quality of the work</p><p>·  Solid leadership skills and a proven ability to build great teams is required</p><p>·  Proven analytical and project management skills<br /><br /><br /><strong>What We Offer</strong><br />·  Senior leadership role with <strong>real decision-making authority</strong><br />·  Opportunity to shape how the business operates<br />·  Exposure to management-level decision making<br /></p>",
